From: pocknix <pocknix@localhost>
Subject: [PATCH] drm/msm/adreno: defer first GPU init until rails settle (ACD 50% clamp)

On SM8550 handhelds (Retroid Pocket 6, and per armada/ROCKNIX the whole
family), if the GPU/GMU first initializes early in boot (any DRM open
triggers the lazy adreno_load_gpu - plymouth's KMS-only splash at ~2-5s
is enough) the power rails are not yet settled and the GMU's ACD
(adaptive clock distribution) latches a "voltage low" state, holding
effective GPU clocks at ~50% for the entire session. devfreq/PLL
counters still report full rate, so this is invisible to every standard
instrument. Measured on RP6: 299 vs 597 GFLOPS (vkbench, exactly 50%);
ROCKNIX only escapes because its slower boot first touches the GPU at
~11.5s.

Defer the first GPU init until boottime passes a threshold. Early DRM
opens simply get no GPU yet - the same benign, well-trodden path as
missing GPU firmware (priv->gpu stays NULL, the open succeeds, every
later open retries). Display/KMS is unaffected, so the boot splash
still works. msm.gpu_init_min_uptime_ms=0 disables the gate.

---
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/msm/adreno/adreno_device.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/msm/adreno/adreno_device.c
@@ -28,6 +28,19 @@
 MODULE_PARM_DESC(no_gpu, "Disable GPU driver register (0=enable GPU driver register (default), 1=skip GPU driver register");
 module_param(skip_gpu, bool, 0400);
 
+/*
+ * If the GPU/GMU first initializes while the power rails are still settling
+ * early in boot, the GMU's ACD latches "voltage low" and holds effective GPU
+ * clocks at ~50% for the whole session while devfreq still reports full rate.
+ * Defer the first (lazy) GPU init until boottime passes this threshold; DRM
+ * opens before then get no GPU yet (same benign path as missing firmware)
+ * and retry on later opens. 0 disables the gate.
+ */
+static unsigned int gpu_init_min_uptime_ms = 12000;
+MODULE_PARM_DESC(gpu_init_min_uptime_ms,
+	"Defer first GPU init until this many ms after boot (default 12000, 0=off)");
+module_param(gpu_init_min_uptime_ms, uint, 0600);
+
 extern const struct adreno_gpulist a2xx_gpulist;
 extern const struct adreno_gpulist a3xx_gpulist;
 extern const struct adreno_gpulist a4xx_gpulist;
@@ -72,6 +85,14 @@
 	struct msm_gpu *gpu = NULL;
 	struct adreno_gpu *adreno_gpu;
 	int ret;
+
+	if (gpu_init_min_uptime_ms &&
+	    ktime_get_boottime_ns() < (u64)gpu_init_min_uptime_ms * NSEC_PER_MSEC) {
+		dev_warn_once(dev->dev,
+			      "deferring GPU init until %u ms uptime (ACD rail settle)\n",
+			      gpu_init_min_uptime_ms);
+		return NULL;
+	}
 
 	if (pdev)
 		gpu = dev_to_gpu(&pdev->dev);
